    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 50,
        "summary": "Asaph speaks of the Second Coming\u2014The Lord accepts the sacrifices of the righteous and will deliver them\u2014Those whose conduct is right will see the salvation of God.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The mighty God, even the Lord, hath spoken, and called the earth from the rising of the sun unto the going down thereof.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God hath shined.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:15.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 33:2.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Our God shall come, and shall not keep silence: a fire shall devour before him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World, End of.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He shall call to the heavens from above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 4:26.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Gather my saints together unto me; those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Saints.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covenants.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 746
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the heavens shall declare his righteousness: for God is judge himself. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 19:1; 97:6.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 21:4; Mosiah 29:12.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear, O my people, and I will speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: I am God, even thy God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:2.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will not reprove thee for thy sacrifices or thy burnt offerings, to have been continually before me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will take no bullock out of thy house, nor he goats out of thy folds.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle upon a thousand hills.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I know all the fowls of the mountains: and the wild beasts of the field are mine.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If I were hungry, I would not tell thee: for the world is mine, and the fulness thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Works of; Stewardship.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Will I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Offer unto God thanksgiving; and pay thy vows unto the most High:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Thanksgiving.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vow.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt glorify me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 38:5 (4\u20135); D&C 100:17.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 81:7.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But unto the wicked God saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes, or that thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0What authority have you.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Seeing thou hatest instruction, and castest my words behind thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou sawest a thief, then thou consentedst with him, and hast been partaker with adulterers.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou givest thy mouth to evil, and thy tongue frameth deceit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou sittest and speakest against thy brother; thou slanderest thine own mother's son.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Slander.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "These things hast thou done, and I kept silence; thou thoughtest that I was altogether such an one as thyself: but I will reprove thee, and set them in order before thine eyes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Ps. 50:21 \u2026 and set covenants in order\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 139
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 148
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Now consider this, ye that forget God, lest I tear you in pieces, and there be none to deliver.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 9:17.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso offereth praise glorifieth me: and to him that ordereth his conversation aright will I shew the salvation of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 61:8.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}